  "prompt": "Does the Tastemaker in Nestl\u00e9 Maggi really contain non-vegetarian substances?",
  "response": "Yes, the Tastemaker in Nestl\u00e9 Maggi noodles can contain non-vegetarian substances, depending on the variant. Some Maggi noodle flavors may include ingredients such as chicken fat or other animal-derived additives. However, many flavors are entirely vegetarian, and Nestl\u00e9 typically labels the packaging to indicate whether a product is vegetarian or not. It's essential to check the ingredient list and look for any vegetarian or non-vegetarian symbols on the packaging to determine the contents of a specific flavor.",
